        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>April 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName>Dr. Solomon&#39;s</persName><lb/> called on me in answer to my letter in relation<lb/> to your debt. He says that he is pressed at<lb/> present but will pay in time&#44; and desires<lb/> me before proceeding to communicate to you.<lb/> I asked him for part of this claim and<lb/> I would give him time for the balance<lb/> this he appears not willing to do. I there<lb/>fore await your answer.</p>
			<p>From what I know of the<lb/> Doctor&#39;s disposition to pay up &#40;entre<lb/> vous&#41; should advise you to in&#61;<lb/>struct me to sue him.</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">H Morrison</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>No. 6 City Hall place</placeName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I know <persName>Morrison</persName> is right<lb/> you&#39;d not obtain a cent <add>&#63;</add> the scoundrel<lb/> <add>&#63;</add>&#44; and if you wish to obtain your<lb/> money it will have be done&#44; why should<lb/> he go to <placeName><hi rend="underline">Stra<add>&#63;</add>berg</hi></placeName>&#63; and buy an estate<lb/> nott you have coming as the journa<add>&#63;</add><lb/> take my advise and you I got your<lb/> money sue him at once. <persName>Mr<lb/> Morrison</persName> with no justice&#44; if the D&#45;<lb/> finds you in earnest&#44; he will pay at once</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">S M Isaacs</persName></p>
			<p><persName>M Levy</persName> from <sic><placeName>Cincinatti</placeName></sic> is engaged<lb/> to a daughter of <persName>John M Davis</persName><lb/> I save two <sic>weedding</sic> <date>sunday 2</date><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> and 2 in the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> is the order of the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> day</p>

          
        </body>
